Tokens

↓

Token IDs

↓

Vectors

↓

Neural Network

This conversion enables the model to perform mathematical operations on language.

Token IDs

Example:

Hello

↓

Token ID = 15496
World

↓

Token ID = 2159

The specific IDs vary by model and tokenizer.

Important Concept

The model never sees the original text.

It sees only token IDs (which are then converted into embeddings before entering the neural network).

Interview Question

Q: Why is tokenization necessary?

Answer:

Tokenization converts text into smaller units that can be represented numerically. Neural networks operate on numerical data, so tokenization is an essential preprocessing step.

Key Takeaways
LLMs process tokens, not raw words.
Tokens are converted into numerical IDs.
Those IDs are transformed into embeddings before being processed by the model.

